# All Purpose Alfredo Sauce
## Ingredients
- 1 stick of unsalted butter
- 16 oz of heavy cream
- 8 oz Parmesan cheese (freshly shredded)
- 2-4 garlic cloves, minced
- Black pepper to taste

## Method
1. In a sauce pan over low-medium heat, melt butter
2. Once butter is melted, add garlic and saute for 60-90 seconds
3. Add Heavy Cream
4. While stirring occasionally, allow sauce to thicken
5. After sauce has thickened slightly, stir in Parmesan cheese until sauce is the right consistency.
6. Add fresh cracked black pepper to taste
7. pour over noodles, protein, vegetables and toss together to combine.

# Variations
## Cajun Seasoniong
### Additional Ingredients
- 2 Tbsp Cajun seasoning
### Method
1. in step 6 add 2 Tbsp of Cajun seasoning along with the black pepper.
